# API Testing Examples

## Products

### 1. Get all products
GET http://localhost:8081/api/products

###

### 2. Get product by ID
GET http://localhost:8081/api/products/1

###

### 3. Search products
GET http://localhost:8081/api/products/search?name=iPhone

###

### 4. Create product
POST http://localhost:8081/api/products
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Sony WH-1000XM5",
  "description": "Premium noise cancelling headphones",
  "price": 399.99,
  "stock": 25
}

###

### 5. Update product
PUT http://localhost:8081/api/products/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "iPhone 15 Pro Max",
  "description": "Latest iPhone with larger display",
  "price": 1299.99,
  "stock": 45
}

###

### 6. Update stock
PATCH http://localhost:8081/api/products/1/stock?quantity=10

###

### 7. Delete product
DELETE http://localhost:8081/api/products/1

###

## Orders

### 1. Get all orders
GET http://localhost:8081/api/orders

###

### 2. Get order by ID
GET http://localhost:8081/api/orders/1

###

### 3. Get orders by status
GET http://localhost:8081/api/orders/status/PENDING

###

### 4. Create order
POST http://localhost:8081/api/orders
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "customerName": "Nguyen Van A",
  "customerEmail": "nguyenvana@example.com",
  "customerPhone": "0987654321",
  "items": [
    {
      "productId": 1,
      "quantity": 2
    },
    {
      "productId": 4,
      "quantity": 1
    }
  ]
}

###

### 5. Update order status
PATCH http://localhost:8081/api/orders/1/status?status=CONFIRMED

###

### 6. Cancel order
POST http://localhost:8081/api/orders/1/cancel

###

